FBIS3-55099 "drsov004_s_94012" FBIS-SOV-94-004 Document Type:Daily Report 6 Jan 1994 Georgia Ministry Rejects Rumors of Armed Forces `Split' LD0501133394 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 1100 GMT 5 Jan 94 LD0501133394 Moscow Russian Television Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By M. Vardzelashvili; from the "Vesti" newscast] [Text] The press center of the Georgian Ministry of Defense has issued a statement in which it rejects rumors circulating in Tbilisi, as well as throughout the republic, that allegedly a split has taken place among the Georgian Armed Forces that could lead to armed conflict. The statement of the press center says that such rumors are absolutely not in accordance with reality. Nevertheless, tension is being felt in Tbilisi, particularly since the explosion in the building of the Ministry of Security. As for the general situation in the republic, measures are continuing in West Georgia to confiscate weapons from the population.
